{
  "text": "The basic idea to prove Theorem 3.2 uses a special Taylor expansion for the operator, which maps a strictly increasing function g with t in the interior of its image to its quantile g \u22121 (t). Details can be found in [CITATION_1] . By this expansion, we obtain the following decomposition m I 1 (t, y) \u2212 m(t, y) = A n (y) + 1 2 B n (y), (5.14)",
  "citation_candidates": [
